          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sunday morning Daniel and I got home from a whirlwind one-week trip to Peru. The trip was amazing! I can't wait to share our pictures and a video I have put together of our adventures in this incredible country.  Unlike my previous "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/category/travel-with-me/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Travel With Me"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " posts, I'm going to break out this trip into multiple posts on various aspects of the trip. With the way I did these posts before, I was packing in too much information into each post which took me too long to put together, and I imagine that they were too long (and sometimes boring) to read through."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/BIRU-WP-20150810T170246GMT-0500.jpg",
              "alt": "8/10/15",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before I start sharing pictures and stories from the trip, I wanted to share what I packed. When I was preparing for this trip, I did a lot of research on what to pack. I was able to pull together a few posts to get what I needed, but I could not find just one post that showed me a solid packing list for one week in Peru during August (their winter) that was not tailored toward hiking on the Inca Trail. I was happy with what I brought along with me, so if you are planning a short trip to Peru during this time of year, hopefully this will help!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For our flights to Peru, we did not check any bags. I fit everything that I needed into a canvas weekender bag and a backpack. We did need to check a bag on the way back to make room for souvenirs, but carry ons were sufficient for everything we needed to bring with us to Peru. One caveat: we stayed the first weekend with my aunt and uncle in Lima, so we were able to do laundry at their apartment the first weekend. You can use laundromats in the larger cities in Peru, have your hotel do some washing for you, or you can pack a couple more items of clothing than I suggest below. Here is what I brought for 8 full days:"
          }
        ]
      },
