          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "We bought the winter hats, headbands, and scarf directly from the women and children who made them on Tequile Island. We bought the two beautiful table runners from a woman in Chinchero after she showed us how she makes them. The llama painting came from a market stand in Cusco. We bought the reed boat figurine and ornament from the people on one of the floating Uros Islands - the boats look just like the actual reed boats the people use."
          }
        ]
